Here, mew can generate a smol version of your current material! This generates a new shader file that is smaller, has less compilation time, and is essentially a snapshot of your current settings. This smol shader is redistributable and doesn't rely on anything else - mew can just move the .shader as you please. It's suggested to always use this for your final materials in order to reduce shader count and improve performance! ^-^ (but don't worry, mew can always go back to the normal shader if you need to make changes)

This feature requires (at minimum) the '{0}' shader variant. Nya!

Shader variants are made in order to help ensure you only include code for the features you need. While other versions may have it (indicated by greyed out tabs or not), this is the "lowest" variant tier that supports it. Please see the docs for more info! ^-^

Super Plug Shader (by VRCFury) is a free mesh deformation system that can be used to deform meshes towards a target, and is a full backwards-compatible replacement for DPS (Dynamic Penetration System by Raliv) and TPS (Thry Penetration System in Poiyomi Pro). In addition to being free, it supports a wide variety of shaders without them needing to hard-code support, including Backlace! Please click the link below to open the documentation for it in order to set it up! Nya!

LTCGI (by _pi_) is a plug-and-play realtime area lighting solution for VRChat. To enable this, please make sure you also include the LTCGI package in your project as it requires its own shader functions to work. When enabled, your material will then automatically use LTCGIs lighting. :3
Standard Specular has no stylised options - try changing the specular mode to see settings here! Nya!
This affect needs to read Depth from the scene! Ensure that your world either has a real-time light enabled or that the Depth Writer prefab is in the scene (provided with Backlace). :3
